            "commit": "cbd9992d513ec4d54fae97182747b2e31681a36e",
            "subject": "LU-9342 pfl: handle uninited component in user defined LOVEA"
          }
        ],
        "author": {
          "name": "Qian Yingjin",
          "email": "qian@ddn.com",
          "date": "2017-04-17 08:05:30.000000000",
          "tz": 480
        },
        "committer": {
          "name": "Oleg Drokin",
          "email": "oleg.drokin@intel.com",
          "date": "2017-04-28 20:36:34.000000000",
          "tz": 0
        },
        "subject": "LU-9356 osd-ldiskfs: add blk_plug when do bio",
        "message": "LU-9356 osd-ldiskfs: add blk_plug when do bio\n\nDuring 16MB bulk RPC I/O evaluation on rhel7, due to kernel\nBIO_MAX_PAGES (256) limit, the 16MB IO is divided into 16 1MB\nI/O submitting to underly block device one by one. And we found\nthat the SFA disk driver got lots of 1MB IOs.\nTo optimize the performance, this patch introduces blk_plug into\nosd-ldiskfs when do bio, before submit IOs, it calls blk_start_plug,\nafter submit all 16MB IOs, calls blk_finish_plug, so that the 16MB\nbulk IO will have more change to merge in the block evelvator\nscheduler layer.\n\nSigned-off-by: Qian Yingjin <qian@ddn.com>\nChange-Id: If26db9f85baf97bc441cc4ad19d5c9f97bd3d7e5\nReviewed-on: https://review.whamcloud.com/26697\nTested-by: Jenkins\nReviewed-by: Alex Zhuravlev <alexey.zhuravlev@intel.com>\nTested-by: Maloo <hpdd-maloo@intel.com>\nReviewed-by: Li Xi <lixi@ddn.com>\nReviewed-by: Oleg Drokin <oleg.drokin@intel.com>\n"
      },
      "branch": "refs/heads/master"
    }
  },
